<t>CREATE TABLE artists (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), genre VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE songs (id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR(255), duration INT, album_id INT, FOREIGN KEY(album_id) REFERENCES albums(id))

CREATE TABLE albums (id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR(255), release_date DATE, artist_id INT, FOREIGN KEY(artist_id) REFERENCES artists(id))</t><s>SELECT artists.name AS artist_name, albums.title AS album_title, songs.title AS song_title FROM artists JOIN albums ON artists.id = albums.artist_id JOIN songs ON albums.id = songs.album_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Song (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, title STRING NOT NULL, duration INT, album_id INT REFERENCES Album(id), artist_id INT REFERENCES Artist(id));

CREATE TABLE Artist (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name STRING NOT NULL, genre STRING);</t><s>select avg(duration) from song where artist_id = 4;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Playlist (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name STRING NOT NULL, description STRING, user_id INT);

CREATE TABLE Song (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, title STRING NOT NULL, duration INT, album_id INT REFERENCES Album(id), artist_id INT REFERENCES Artist(id));

CREATE TABLE Artist (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name STRING NOT NULL, genre STRING);

<t>CREATE TABLE Artist (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name STRING NOT NULL, genre STRING);

CREATE TABLE Album (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, title STRING NOT NULL, release_date DATE, artist_id INT REFERENCES Artist(id));

CREATE TABLE Song (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, title STRING NOT NULL, duration INT, album_id INT REFERENCES Album(id), artist_id INT REFERENCES Artist(id));

<t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT * FROM artists</s>

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><s>select * from artists</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL

<t>CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><s>select artist_name from artists</s>

);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_id INT,

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><s>select artist_id, artist_name from artists</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    album_id INT,

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

);

    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><s>select artist_id, artist_name from artists</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,

);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><s>SELECT album_name FROM albums</s>

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

<t>CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)

CREATE TABLE albums (

    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT album_name, release_date FROM albums</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT album_name, release_date FROM albums</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><s>select * from songs</s>

CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT song_id, song_name FROM songs</s>

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

<t>CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><s>SELECT genre_name FROM genres</s>

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    album_id INT,

);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

);

    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT genre_id FROM song_genre</s>

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),

);

    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT genre_id FROM song_genre</s>

    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT genre_id FROM song_genre</s>

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>select song_id, genre_id from song_genre</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT song_id, genre_id FROM song_genre</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT s.song_name, a.album_name FROM songs s JOIN albums a ON s.album_id = a.album_id</s>

    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,

    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT s.song_name, g.genre_name FROM songs s JOIN song_genre sg ON s.song_id = sg.song_id JOIN genres g ON sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</s>

    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><s>SELECT s.song_name, g.genre_name FROM songs s JOIN song_genre sg ON s.song_id = sg.song_id JOIN genres g ON sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

<t>CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,

    song_id INT,

    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);
</t><s>select s.song_name, g.genre_name from songs s join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);

    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><s>SELECT s.song_name, g.genre_name FROM songs s JOIN song_genre sg ON s.song_id = sg.song_id JOIN genres g ON sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);

    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><s>select s.song_name, g.genre_name from songs s join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);

    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);
</t><s>select a.artist_name, g.genre_name from artists a join albums al on a.artist_id = al.artist_id join songs s on al.album_id = s.album_id join song_genre sg on s.song_id = sg.song_id join genres g on sg.genre_id = g.genre_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE artists (
    artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    artist_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE songs (
    song_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    song_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    album_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES albums(album_id)
);


CREATE TABLE albums (
    album_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    album_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    release_date DATE,
    artist_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
);


CREATE TABLE genres (
    genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);


CREATE TABLE song_genre (
    song_id INT,
    genre_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (song_id, genre_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (song_id) REFERENCES songs(song_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES genres(genre_id)
);
